The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes an unsupervised metric learning approach, which involves learning a projection for each view, and thus, it is likely to fall under machine learning (cs.LG) as well. The paper also involves clustering, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with matching and retrieval of images, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR).
